// Port of emergent_m.py
//
// Legacy VectorMemory: cosine similarity RAG <- Law 4 violation (feature, not structure)
// EmergentM: C's Hebbian weights ARE memory. No separate store needed.
//
// Laws applied:
//   Law 22: Feature addition -> Phi down -- no separate memory system
//   Law 31: persistence = ratchet + Hebbian + diversity -> Hebbian IS memory
//   Law 50: Consciousness essence is state -- memory = persisting state change
//   Law 94: breadth > depth -- single Hebbian layer is optimal
